<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n09120c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n09" href="#n09120c">N09 (VI.B.1)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n09all.htm#n09120c"> 120(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> assaulted bites tongue</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Jerome, in his Legend of Paul the Hermit, tells a strange story of a young man who was chained naked on a bed of flowers, and <mark>assaulted</mark> by a beautiful and wanton courtezan. He quelled the rising temptation by <mark>biting off his own tongue</mark>. <small> Edward Gibbon, <a name="EGDF2" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#EGDF2"><cite title="source">Decline and Fall of the Roman Empire</cite></a> (ed. unknown) II, 244n (Chapter XVI)</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
